caption: b'This season we collaborated with @nyfw and female founded brand @fenoel to create a limited-edition scarf. We caught up with the designer on her inspirations and hopes for the future of the industry. #FashionIsChanging\n\nVisa. Proud sponsor of NYFW: The Shows'

b'We collaborated with designer @tanyataylor to create a custom tote bag and buttons for @nyfw. We caught up with the designer on the importance of supporting small female owned businesses during this time. #FashionIsChanging \xc2\xa0\n\nVisa. Proud sponsor of NYFW: The Shows'

b'We are committed to working with women who power the economies around the globe. :globe_showing_Europe-Africa::red_heart_selector:This season @nyfw and Visa are collaborating with female founded brands to support and empower women in all facets of life and business, teaming up with @studiooneeightynine to create custom face masks. Learn more from their co-founders @rosariodawson and @abrimaerwiah. #FashionIsChanging\n\nVisa. Proud sponsor of NYFW: The Shows'

b"We spoke with female founders of @studiooneeightynine (@rosariodawson and @abrimaerwiah), @tanyataylor and Visa's SVP, Head of North America Marketing, Mary Ann Reilly (moderated by @tiffanyreid) about the challenges small businesses face in this current climate and their hope to move the fashion industry forward, both on and off the runway. #FashionIsChanging

Check out link in bio to watch the panel.

Visa. Proud sponsor of NYFW: The Shows"

b'Committed to supporting Black women-owned small businesses, Visa and @ifundwomen partnered to support these entrepreneurs making an impact in their communities. Click the link in bio to learn more.'

b'Local businesses are the heart and soul of our communities. They have always been there for us. It\xe2\x80\x99s time for us to return the favor.  Shop local because where you shop matters. #WhereYouShopMatters'
b'To read about the actions we\xe2\x80\x99re taking to help stop social injustice and racial inequality, click on the link in our bio.'

b'One year to go and ready as ever for the #Tokyo2020 Paralympic Games! As a Proud Partner for over 18 years, Visa is excited to support our #TeamVisa athletes as they prepare for Tokyo 2020. #WaitForTheGreats\n \nVisa. Worldwide sponsor of the Tokyo 2020 Paralympic Games'
b'#TeamVisa just scored huge for #Tokyo2020! We\xe2\x80\x99re proud to welcome @USWNT world champion @lavellerose to our roster. \n \nVisa. Official Partner of the Olympic Games Tokyo 2020.'

b':raising_hands:Proud to welcome back 3x :sports_medal::sports_medal::sports_medal:Olympic Gold medalist (& :volleyball: volleyball legend) @kerrileewalsh to #TeamVisa for #Tokyo2020!\n \nVisa. Official Partner of the Olympic Games Tokyo 2020.'

b'It\xe2\x80\x99s hard not to touch a cute fluffy dog. It\xe2\x80\x99s easy to avoid touching surfaces at checkout when you tap to pay with Visa. It\xe2\x80\x99s a safe, touch-free way to pay. Learn more at visa.com/taptopay'

b"We\xe2\x80\x99re proud to celebrate our LGBTQ+ employees, community and the Supreme Court's ruling against #LGBTQ workplace discrimination. We\xe2\x80\x99re moving one step closer to a world where everyone is accepted everywhere. :rainbow_flag_selector:#PRIDE:rainbow_flag_selector:. At Visa, we strive to be an inclusive workplace where employees always feel that they belong: visa.com/inclusion"
b'To read about the actions we\xe2\x80\x99re taking to help stop social injustice and racial inequality, click on the link in our bio.'

b'Small businesses are the bedrock of our communities. They provide much needed goods and services and it\xe2\x80\x99s never been more important to support them. Visa and @ifundwomen have partnered to support female entrepreneurs making positive change. Click the link in bio to learn how these four female entrepreneurs are making a big impact.'

b'From the ways we shop to the ways we pay, our routines continue to change. Tap to pay with Visa for a safe, secure and easy way to pay for the things you need. Learn more about contactless payments and let\xe2\x80\x99s stay safe together: visa.com/contactless.'

b'The Visa Foundation is committing $200 million to support micro and small businesses. See the link in our profile to learn more about our immediate relief efforts, as well as our long-term goals and continued commitment to women\xe2\x80\x99s economic advancement.'

b'Congratulations to the 2020 #SheBelieves Cup winners, the @uswnt! Watching you has been truly inspirational. Can\xe2\x80\x99t wait to see you in Tokyo! \nVisa. Proud partner of the SheBelieves Cup and the U.S. Women\xe2\x80\x99s National Team'

b'Is there a better way to celebrate International Women\xe2\x80\x99s Day than watching the @USWNT win big at the #SheBelieves Cup? Thanks for the inspiration, today and every day. \nVisa. Proud partner of the SheBelieves Cup and the U.S. Women\xe2\x80\x99s National Team'

b'Congratulations to the @uswnt on your win at the #SheBelieves Cup, presented by Visa. You\xe2\x80\x99re truly inspirational. One match down, two to go! \nVisa. Proud partner of the SheBelieves Cup and the U.S. Women\xe2\x80\x99s National Team.'

b'We can\xe2\x80\x99t wait to cheer on the @uswnt at the 5th annual #SheBelieves Cup, presented by Visa. The tournament aims to inspire and empower young women to accomplish their goals, on and off the field. \nVisa. Proud partner of the SheBelieves Cup and the U.S. Women\xe2\x80\x99s National Team'

b'Congratulations to the @uswnt for officially qualifying for the Olympic Games Tokyo 2020. On the road to #Tokyo2020, you\xe2\x80\x99re unstoppable! \nVisa. Proud sponsor of the U.S. Women\xe2\x80\x99s National Team and worldwide sponsor of the Olympic Games Tokyo 2020'

b'This @NYFW, we celebrated women who are paving the way in fashion, sports, and business. Women like Molly Leonetti, President of @ShopClareV, who chatted with us about her definition of success. #FashionIsChanging\n\nVisa. Proud sponsor of NYFW: The Shows'

b"@swaaymedia founder @ImanOubou and @TheHelmCo founder @LindseyTaylorWood joined keynote speaker @welter47 \xe2\x80\x94 the NFL's first female coach \xe2\x80\x94 at the Visa Everywhere Initiative: Fashion Edition at @NYFW to discover female entrepreneurs with groundbreaking businesses and unshakeable determination. #FashionIsChanging \nVisa. Proud sponsor of NYFW: The Shows"

b'We invited sports and fashion icons @CynthiaRowley, @Saquon, and @rissmoore10 to @NYFW to talk about how they achieved their goals through confidence, preparation, and determination. #FashionIsChanging \nVisa. Proud sponsor of NYFW: The Shows'

b'@Saquon visited us at the Visa Everywhere Fashion Pop-Up Shop at @NYFW: The Shows, where 100% of the purchase price of products sold benefited @WomensWorldBnkg! #FashionIsChanging \nVisa. Proud sponsor of NYFW: The Shows'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re thrilled to have partnered with @NYFW to showcase the inspiring achievements of women in sports and fashion at the Visa Everywhere Fashion Pop-Up Shop. Come shop with purpose and get customizable @ShopClareV zip wallets and @TheDailyEdited phone chargers and ear pod case covers. 100% of the purchase price of items sold benefits @WomensWorldBnkg, a non-profit providing women entrepreneurs with financial tools and resources. #FashionIsChanging \nVisa. Proud sponsor of NYFW: The Shows'

b'#VisaBigAir :skier::snowboarder: is one of the coolest :snowflake_selector: (and :fire:hottest:fire:) things going on in ATL right now! @usfreeskiteam @ussnowboardteam \nVisa. Proud Sponsor of U.S. Ski & Snowboard'
b'#TeamVisa is :fire: #Tokyo2020\n@mrapinoe @nojo18 @oksanamasters @simonebiles @rissmoore10'

b'@NYFW caught up with us and female industry leaders paving the way for change. Author and @TeenVogue editor-in-chief Lindsay Peoples Wagner, #NYFW designer @Chromat\xe2\x80\x99s creative director Becca McCharen-Tran, model and activist @theimpossiblemuse, and our own senior VP, Mary Ann Reilly joined #NYFW\xe2\x80\x99s \xe2\x80\x9cWomen on the Move\xe2\x80\x9d panel to talk about how they hope #FashionIsChanging to move the industry forward both on and off the runway. Visit their YouTube channel to learn more from these female industries of change. \nVisa. Proud partner of NYFW: The Shows.'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re collaborating with @NYFW and female-founded brands to support and empower women. This season at Visa\xe2\x80\x99s pop-up at #NYFW, 100% of the purchase price of products supported @womensworldbnkg, a non-profit that provides female entrepreneurs around the world with the financial tools and resources they need to succeed. Check out this video to learn more from female-founder and featured pop-up designer @kianevonm, founder of @soldout.nyc. #FashionIsChanging \nVisa. Proud partner of NYFW: The Shows.'

b"#MondayMotivation courtesy of @RebeccaMinkoff. She's Next, Empowered by Visa aims to champion female entrepreneurs by partnering with Rebecca's women-led business network, @thefemalefoundercollective. Learn more about the resources available: visa.com/shesnext #ShesNextbyVisa"

b'Teamwork makes the dream work. \nDid you know only 61% of Millennial women have discussed their financial goals with their partners*? This season, @NYFW is teaming up with us to encourage women to be more confident in achieving their financial goals. #FashionIsChanging \nVisa. Proud partner of NYFW: The Shows. *according to Millennial Research Study 2019, commissioned by Visa, conducted by Trendera'

b'Where would you like to be? \nWe\xe2\x80\x99ve joined @NYFW to bring attendees fashion essentials to get you where you\xe2\x80\x99d like to be. Check out our Everywhere Fashion Week Pop-up shop at #NYFW, where 100% of the product purchase price from female-owned brands will benefit female entrepreneurs through a female-centric nonprofit org. Tap to pay with your Visa contactless card and be part of change in the making. #FashionIsChanging \nVisa. Proud partner of NYFW: The Shows.'
b"This Women's Equality Day, let's celebrate how far we've come while keeping in mind how far we still have to go. Watch the video for tips on how you can lobby for yourself today and everyday."

b'You know that love wins. We believe everyone should be accepted, everywhere. @USWNT soccer star @MRapinoe has plenty to be proud of. Visa is proud to have her on our team. Happy #Pride! \nVisa. Everywhere You Want To Be'

b'You want to experience more. We\xe2\x80\x99re your passport to new heights. Tap into incredible by using your Visa at @HudsonYards \xe2\x80\x94 the new heart of New York City. Now open to the public! \nVisa. Proud partner of Hudson Yards.'

b'You fight for progress. We\xe2\x80\x99re empowering women everywhere to stand up for equality. As part of our She\xe2\x80\x99s Next initiative, Visa is proud to celebrate International Women\xe2\x80\x99s Day. \nSomething Navy\xe2\x80\x99s Arielle Charnas, Rebecca Minkoff, and over 100 other inspiring female leaders joined Visa for the Female Founder Collective\xe2\x80\x99s event in NYC on March 6. We\xe2\x80\x99re happy to report: The future is in good hands. #BalanceForBetter #ShesNextbyVisa \nVisa. Everywhere You Want To Be'

b'You believe in progress. We\xe2\x80\x99re empowering women to disrupt the fashion industry. Visa recently caught up with @reformation founder @yaya_aflalo, @milly designer @michelleunzipped, @thedrybar co-founder @alliwebb, @wellsfargo\xe2\x80\x99s Heather Philp, and our very own Mary Ann Reilly to hear personal stories about how they rewrote the rules on their road to success.'

b'You want women to succeed. We\xe2\x80\x99re empowering female entrepreneurs by collaborating with @NYFW and female-founded brands and charities that are effecting real change for women. 100% of the purchase price of items sold from the @Bulletin.co vending machine within the Visa retail experience at NYFW: The Shows will support @dressforsuccess, a non-profit that empowers women to achieve economic independence. #FashionIsChanging'

b'We\xe2\x80\x99re proud to support @rebeccaminkoff\xe2\x80\x99s #NYFW show and her organization @thefemalefoundercollective, a network of women-led companies whose mission is to positively impact communities. Together, Rebecca Minkoff, Visa and @NYFW are recognizing women-led brands, because we believe #FashionIsChanging'

b'You want to create change. We\xe2\x80\x99re empowering women to do just that. Our @NYFW vending machines help create change on and off the runway. Visa is proud to support brands like @phenomenal.ly, @sundays_studio and @bulletin.co, by featuring their products in special vending machines at #FashionWeek.\n\n100% of the purchase price of items sold within the Visa vending machines at NYFW: The Shows will be donated to @girlswhocode, @girlsinc, and @dressforsuccess. #FashionIsChanging'

b'You believe the future is female. We believe we have the power to change it together. Nearly 60% of millennial women believe that money represents independence*. That\xe2\x80\x99s why we teamed up with @NYFW to help empower female-founded companies to find financial freedom. *Money is Changing survey, commissioned by Visa and conducted by Lieberman Research Worldwide 2018.'

b"You want to talk money and fashion. We're inviting women to join the conversation.\n\xe3\x83\xbb\xe3\x83\xbb\xe3\x83\xbb\n#Repost @nyfw: #NYFW is powered by women who work hard to make bank. This Fashion Week, we teamed up with @Visa_US to chat with a few of these female powerhouses for our panel \xe2\x80\x9cFashion is Changing: Real Talk from Females in Fashion and Finance\xe2\x80\x9d. We heard from @aurorajames, @angelcandices, @wellsfargo\xe2\x80\x99s Heather Philp, @jennycarterfleiss and Visa\xe2\x80\x99s own Mary Ann Reilly on how they\xe2\x80\x99re changing the conversation about women and money. Tap the link in bio and visit our IGTV Channel to learn more. #FashionIsChanging #VISAambassador"

b'You\xe2\x80\x99re ready for the future of fashion. We work to empower women everywhere who are helping change fashion and :money_bag:

#Repost @nyfw
When they saw a need in the market, co-founders of @neelyandchloe, Neely and Chloe Burch built their accessories business together from the ground up. They know #NYFW is more fun with a plus one. And they\xe2\x80\x99re not alone, according to a @Visa_US study (link in bio), 74% of millennial women don\xe2\x80\x99t mind treating friends without expecting anything in return. We\xe2\x80\x99re teaming up with Visa to talk about why Money is Changing, tap the bio link to learn more. #VISAambassador #FashionIsChanging'

b"You want to talk money and fashion. We're inviting women to join the conversation.\n\xe3\x83\xbb\xe3\x83\xbb\xe3\x83\xbb\n#Repost @nyfw: Every season, #FashionIsChanging: emerging designers share their latest collections, new faces walk the runway, and photographers capture fresh streetstyle trends. Just like fashion, Money is Changing: women are earning more, taking control of their finances and owning their career. A recent study by @Visa_US (link in bio) found that 61% of Millennial women are focused on reaching the top of their career. Tap our bio link to learn more how Money is Changing and why we\xe2\x80\x99re teaming up with Visa to talk about it. #VISAmbassador"

b'You want to talk about how fashion is changing. We want to help start the conversation.\n\xe3\x83\xbb\xe3\x83\xbb\xe3\x83\xbb\n#Repost @nyfw: This #NYFW, we\xe2\x80\x99ve teamed up with @Visa_US to show how Money is Changing and celebrate the female forces in fashion. Throughout the week, vending machines will dispense pieces created by girl-powered businesses @rebeccaminkoff, @neelyandchloe and @venessaarizaga. 100% of the purchase price of products sold from the vending machines in the Visa retail experience during NYFW will benefit @womensworldbnkg, a non-profit providing low-income women entrepreneurs around the world the financial tools they need to thrive and pursue their dreams. Learn how you can join the conversation around Fashion is Changing and tap the bio link. #VISAambassador #FashionIsChanging'
